Bink's Scottsdale is a wonderful restaurant tucked into the corner of a small mall. My wife and I came for the appetizer and stayed for lunch. The app in question was the Sweetbread nuggets. These golden-brown delights were cooked to perfection and paired with a great sweet & sour sauce.  My wife had the Chicken Salad sandwich which she enjoyed. I had the Ham sandwich which was also very good. Both sandwiches came with fresh pickles and great dipping sauces for the accompanying fries. A very delightful lunch.  We hope to try dinner soon and visit some of Binkley's other valley restaurants.

